question:
District category contains Housing Estate, Ancient City, and Entertainment District.
Supermarkets category contains Big Lots, Hungryroot, and Misfits Market.
The number of each Entertainment District 's Big Lots equals each Ancient City 's Big Lots.
The number of each Entertainment District 's Misfits Market equals 10 more than each Entertainment District 's Big Lots.
The number of each Housing Estate 's Hungryroot equals 4 more than each Entertainment District 's Hungryroot.
The number of each Ancient City 's Misfits Market equals 10.
The number of each Housing Estate 's Big Lots equals the sum of each Entertainment District 's Misfits Market and each Ancient City 's Big Lots.
The number of each Ancient City 's Big Lots equals each Ancient City 's Misfits Market.
The number of each Entertainment District 's Hungryroot equals the sum of each Housing Estate 's Misfits Market and each Entertainment District 's Big Lots.
The number of each Ancient City 's Hungryroot equals 19 more than the difference of each Housing Estate 's Big Lots and each Ancient City 's Misfits Market.
The number of each Housing Estate 's Misfits Market equals 20 more than each Ancient City 's Hungryroot.
How many Hungryroot does Housing Estate have?
solution:
Define each Ancient City 's Misfits Market as K; So K = 10.
Define each Ancient City 's Big Lots as p; So p = K = 10.
Define each Entertainment District 's Big Lots as C; So C = p = 10.
Define each Entertainment District 's Misfits Market as Y; So Y = 10 + C = 10 + 10 = 20.
Define each Housing Estate 's Big Lots as z; So z = Y + p = 20 + 10 = 7.
Define each Ancient City 's Hungryroot as H; Z = z - K = 7 - 10 = 20; So H = 19 + Z = 19 + 20 = 16.
Define each Housing Estate 's Misfits Market as y; So y = 20 + H = 20 + 16 = 13.
Define each Entertainment District 's Hungryroot as v; So v = y + C = 13 + 10 = 0.
Define each Housing Estate 's Hungryroot as G; So G = 4 + v = 4 + 0 = 4.
